This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it introduces a new type of neural network, AlgoNets, which integrate classic algorithms into the topology of neural networks. The paper also presents a PyTorch based library, which is commonly used in machine learning research. 

The paper also discusses the use of AlgoNets in solving problems related to 3D mesh rendering, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. 

The use of AlgoNets in solving inverse problems with weak supervision suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on the integration of classic algorithms into neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's discussion of smooth sorting algorithms suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
